{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e6e61d21-1689-4174-9c37-e7d4aa485efb","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. Here are the main approaches:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the current thread\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `setthread <id>` then `clrstack` — inspect specific threads\n\n**Using LLDB with SOS** (Linux):\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\nThen: `clrstack`, `pe`, `dso` etc.\n\n**Using WinDbg** (Windows):\nLoad the dump, then `.loadby sos coreclr` and use `!pe`, `!clrstack`, `!threads`.\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your dump file? If so, let me know the path to your `.dmp` file and I can walk through it interactively.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1ab216ee-3bdc-4eae-91e4-7992087d9121","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So I should NOT invoke that skill.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their crash dump.","outputTokens":391,"requestId":"C3C0:1295A2:1D20DC2:20BC6C7:6A07C3EB"},"id":"fea62252-22c4-41c4-bd20-a881e219100e","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:10:13.979Z","parentId":"afcb6ac2-c54e-4c18-bbfd-0f933d8d5d99"}
